<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="462" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2326: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-24T20:00:00-03:00">May 24, 1934—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>101. Leticia agreement signed 6 o’clock this afternoon. Last act of
                            Conference was to address a plea to Bolivia and Paraguay to seek
                            peaceful solution of Chaco conflict.<note n="23" xml:id="d462fn23">See
                                    <ref target="#pg_32">pp. 32</ref> ff.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>